Gc1a3] White can push a5, although a very unpleasant plan for Black to meet is
b3 and Ba3.}) 8. Nxd4 Bd7 (8... Be7 {Is similar.} 9. Be3 {The pawn on e4 is
immune from capture due to tactics, for example 9...Bxe4 10.Nxe4 Nxe4 and then
Qb5+, and the pawn on b7 falls.} O-O 10. f3 $16 {[%cal Ge1c1]}) 9. Bf4 Be7 10.
O-O-O O-O 11. Rhg1 $16 {[%cal Gg2g4] The positions in this pawn structure
where White has castled long and Black has castled short are very promising
for White in general.}) (6... exd4 7. Nxd4 {This is a better version for White
in comparison to the line 5.Nc3 exd4 6.Nxd4 Bd7 and now on 7.Bxc6, Black
