{[%evp 0,39,21,16,22,17,13,14,14,3,18,17,17,-69,61,45,7,25,3,9,35,61,50,27,24,
23,38,34,31,26,26,26,31,36,35,35,35,23,23,19,26,27]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5
Bc5 {Although this is a rarer move, a lot of theory has been developed in this
line. Recently, this move is mostly used in blitz and rapid games.} 4. c3 {
Trying to push d4 with tempo.} Nf6 (4... f5 {This is very similar to the
Jaenisch gambit, although here Bc5 and c3 are included which is in White's
favor, as d4 is coming with tempo.} 5. d4 fxe4 (5... exd4 {Black's idea is
after White plays 6.cxd4 to give a check with 6...Bb4+, however, White has a
better option.} 6. e5 $1 {The game is already difficult for Black.} dxc3 (6...
a6 {Doesn't change much and it's similar to the position in the main line.} 7.
Ba4 dxc3 8. Nxc3 d6 9. O-O $16) 7. Nxc3 Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Nd5 $16 {[%csl Ge5]
Black's king safety has been compromised with the f5 push and White's pawn on
e5 is hindering the development of Black's pieces. In addition, Bg5 is an idea
for White.}) 6. Bxc6 {The best move, aiming to get the maximum out of the
position.} (6. dxc5 {This is also possible and leads to a comfortable
advantage for White.} exf3 7. Qxf3 Nf6 8. O-O O-O 9. Bg5 $14) 6... dxc6 (6...
exf3 $6 7. Bxf3 exd4 8. O-O $16 {[%csl Re8][%cal Gf1e1]}) 7. Nxe5 Bd6 (7... Qd5
{Has been played in some games.} 8. O-O Nf6 9. f4 Bd6 10. c4 Qe6 11. Nc3 O-O
12. c5 $1 Bxe5 13. dxe5 Nd5 14. Nxe4 Qg6 15. Qe1 $16 {[%cal Ga2a4,Ga1a3] Black
has some compensation for the pawn due to the control of the light squares e6
and f5, however, it's not enough. White can play a4 and Ra3 next, with the
idea to swing the rook over to the kingside.}) 8. Qh5+ {It's a good idea to
provoke g6.} g6 9. Qe2 Bf5 10. Bf4 Qe7 11. Nd2 Nf6 12. O-O O-O-O 13. f3 $5 (13.
Rae1 c5 14. Ndc4 {Is another option that White can play.}) 13... exf3 (13...
Nd5 14. Bg3 {Doesn't change much in the position.}) 14. Ndxf3 Rde8 15. Rae1 $16
{All of White's pieces are well placed and the knight on e5 is very strong.
White can continue with c4 later on.}) (4... Nge7 {This makes more sense when
a6 and Ba4 are included, as the bishop from c5 will have a retreat square on
a7. With this move, Black is preparing against the move 5.d4, so it's a good
idea to postpone it.} 5. O-O $1 {It's important to start with this move. White
wants to continue with d4 next.} (5. d4 exd4 6. cxd4 Bb4+ {Black will more or
less equalize.} 7. Bd2 (7. Nc3 d5) 7... Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2 d5 9. exd5 Nxd5 10. Bxc6+
bxc6 11. O-O O-O 12. Nc3 {White's advantage is microscopic and the game
eventually ended in a draw.} Nxc3 13. Qxc3 Be6 14. Ne5 Bd5 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16.
Qxc6 Qxd4 $11 {1/2-1/2 (39) Anand,V (2753) -Carlsen,M (2863) chess24.com INT
2020}) 5... Bb6 (5... a6 {There is no need to play Ba4 and transpose to the
other line where a6 and Ba4 have been included, as White has a better option.}
6. Bxc6 Nxc6 7. d4 exd4 8. cxd4 Ba7 9. d5 Ne7 10. d6 cxd6 11. Nc3 $16 {[%csl
Rd6][%cal Gc1f4]}) (5... d5 {This simply loses a pawn for Black.} 6. Nxe5 O-O (
6... dxe4 $2 7. Nxf7 $18 {[%cal Gd1h5]}) 7. Bxc6 Nxc6 (7... bxc6 8. d4 Bd6 9.
exd5 cxd5 10. Bf4 $16 {[%cal Gb1d2,Gf1e1]}) 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. d4 $16 {And e5 can
be played after Bd6. Black has minimal compensation for the pawn with the
bishop pair, but it's nowhere near anything tangible.}) (5... Ng6 6. d4 Bb6 {
Transposes to 5...Bb6.}) 6. d4 exd4 (6... Ng6 {This is also possible. This
version without the moves a6 and Ba4 is better for White, and the best way to
use that is to play:} 7. a4 $1 {Threatening Bxc6 and a4-a5.} a6 8. Bxc6 $1 (8.
Bc4 {This may be slightly better for White, however, it leads to a complex
position, so it's simpler to capture the pawn instead.} h6 9. Be3 O-O 10. Nbd2
d6 $13) 8... dxc6 9. a5 Ba7 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 11. dxe5 {Black has some minimal
compensation but it's not enough.} Qxd1 (11... Qe7 12. Qf3 Qxe5 13. Bf4 Qe7 14.
Qg3 O-O 15. Nd2 $16 {[%csl Rc7,Ge4] Protecting the pawn on e4. White has a
very good pawn structure and Black is simply worse.}) 12. Rxd1 Bg4 13. Rd3 O-O
14. Bf4 $16) 7. cxd4 d5 (7... a6 8. Bc4 $16 {With the idea to push d4-d5 next.}
